    <div class="story-card__description">
                
        <h3 class="story-card__hed" >
            <a href="https://www.propublica.org/article/how-america-waged-global-campaign-against-baby-formula-regulation-thailand">
                                    The U.S. Government Defended the Overseas Business Interests of Baby Formula Makers. Kids Paid the Price.
                            </a>
        </h3>

        <p class="story-card__dek" >
                            Records and interviews show that the U.S. government repeatedly used its muscle to advance the interests of large baby formula companies while thwarting the efforts of Thailand and other developing countries to safeguard children’s health.
                    </p>

        <p class="story-card__byline">
            by <a class="name" href="https://www.propublica.org/people/heather-vogell">Heather Vogell</a>, ProPublica, photography by <span class="name">June Watsamon Tri-yasakda</span>, special to <a href="https://www.propublica.org">ProPublica</a>,             <time class="timestamp" datetime="2024-03-21EDT05:00">March 21, 5 a.m. EDT</time>
        </p>

            </div>
</div>
